Bug: Komodo crashes on startup (SIGSEGV inside
hb_unicode_funcs_destroy, called from hb_buffer_t::reset() via
hb_buffer_create(), gfx/harfbuzz/src/hb-unicode.cc /
gfx/harfbuzz/src/hb-buffer.cc) under modern GCC (15+).

This vendored harfbuzz version relies on `if (unlikely (!this ||
this->is_inert ())) return false;` guards at the top of several
hb_object_header_t methods (hb-object-private.hh) to make calls like
hb_unicode_funcs_destroy(nullptr) -- which legitimately happens on
every hb_buffer_create(), since hb_buffer_t::reset() unconditionally
destroys the (still null, freshly calloc'd) `unicode` field before
setting it -- safe no-ops.

Modern GCC's more aggressive undefined-behavior-based optimization is
allowed to delete "this == nullptr" checks inside non-static member
functions entirely, since invoking a non-static member function
through a null pointer is itself undefined behavior by the C++
standard -- and at -Os, it does, turning this into a real null-pointer
dereference. Build this directory with -fno-delete-null-pointer-checks
to keep the guards the code relies on.
Index: gfx/harfbuzz/src/moz.build
--- a/gfx/harfbuzz/src/moz.build	Thu Jan 08 23:22:45 2015 -0500
+++ b/gfx/harfbuzz/src/moz.build	Sun Jul 12 13:36:02 2026 +0800
@@ -60,6 +60,18 @@
 
 MSVC_ENABLE_PGO = True
 
+if CONFIG['GNU_CC'] or CONFIG['GNU_CXX']:
+    # This harfbuzz version relies on `if (unlikely (!this || ...))
+    # return false;` guards at the top of several hb_object_header_t
+    # methods to make calls like hb_unicode_funcs_destroy(nullptr) (hit
+    # on every hb_buffer_create(), via hb_buffer_t::reset()) safe
+    # no-ops. Modern GCC's more aggressive UB-based optimization is
+    # allowed to -- and does, at -Os -- delete "this == nullptr" checks
+    # entirely, since invoking a non-static member function through a
+    # null pointer is itself undefined behavior, turning this into a
+    # real null-pointer crash. Keep the checks.
+    CXXFLAGS += ['-fno-delete-null-pointer-checks']
+
 FINAL_LIBRARY = 'gkmedias'
 
 DEFINES['PACKAGE_VERSION'] = '"moz"'
